        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1966-03-22T14:14:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1966-03-22T14:14:00-05:00" n="264"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d264">
                <head>264. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Saudi Arabia</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d264fn1">Source: National Archives and Records
                        Administration, RG 59, Central Files 1964-66, DEF 12-5 SAUD. Secret;
                        Priority; <gloss target="#t_Limdis1">Limdis</gloss>. Drafted by Korn;
                        cleared by <persName corresp="#p_SHM1">Symmes</persName>, Judd, Colonel
                        Byrd, and <persName>Meyers</persName>; and approved by <persName
                            corresp="#p_DRP1">Davies</persName>. Repeated to London, Cairo, Taiz,
                        and <gloss target="#t_CINCSTRIKE1">CINCSTRIKE</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1966-03-22T14:14:00-05:00">March 22, 1966, 2:14 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>548. Re <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 520.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d264fn2">See <ref target="#d263fn3">footnote 3, Document
                        263</ref>.</note> Following is summary Secretary’s March 17 letter to
                    British Ambassador in reply <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> demarche March 12
                    (text being pouched): <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>
                            <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> shares <gloss target="#t_UK1"
                                >UK</gloss> desire that <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss>/US air
                            defense sales Saudi Arabia be carried out without change.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>However sending squadron <gloss target="#t_RAF1">RAF</gloss> aircraft
                            to Saudi Arabia under present circumstances would have seriously
                            disturbing effect on Saudi-<gloss target="#t_UAR1">UAR</gloss>
                            negotiations regarding Yemen. Could be disservice to <gloss
                                target="#t_SAG1">SAG</gloss> since would invite hostile propaganda
                            attacks by <gloss target="#t_UAR1">UAR</gloss> and others. Introduction
                                <gloss target="#t_RAF1">RAF</gloss> units or employment British
                            subjects to fly Saudi aircraft in combat operations would not be in US,
                                <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> or Saudi interest.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>US would naturally be most concerned should Saudi integrity be
                            threatened. However, US commitment is of strictly limited nature. Has
                            been made clear to Faisal it does not extend to providing military cover
                            for Saudi operations in support of hostilities in Yemen or to any Saudi
                            actions of provocative nature.</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>We hope report Prince Sultan’s apparent satisfaction at <gloss
                                target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> offer supply limited number Lightning MKI
                            and Hunter MK6 aircraft at early date is indication that Saudis will not
                            press for <gloss target="#t_RAF1">RAF</gloss> units or put forward other
                            request which could disturb current delicate balance in Near
                            East.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RD3">
                            <hi rend="strong">Rusk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
